/emergency, UIC promotes:   Protection of life, property, and the environment;  Support of the health and safety of students, faculty, staff, and visitors;  Protection of critical infrastructure assets, and facilities;  Maintenance of university services;  Restoration of essential programs and general university operations; and  Mineralization of the disruption of university operations and activities.       Compliance        Emergency Management          Violence Prevention          Clery Compliance          Continuity of Operations          Threat/Hazard Mitigation          Training & Exercising          Governance        Executive Teams          Compliance              PLANNING    Back to main content           Emergency Management     Emergency Operations Plan    Annexes    Emergency Operations Policy Group    Practice Standards      Violence Prevention     Violence Prevention Plan     Behavioral Threat Assessments Teams     BTAT Process    Behavioral Threat Assessment Team for Employees (BTAT-E)    Behavioral Threat Assessment Team for Students (BTAT-S)        Violence Prevention Governance     Members of the Behavioral Threat Assessment Team for  Employees (BTAT-E)    Members of the Behavioral Threat Assessment Team for Students (BTAT-S)      Practice Standards      Clery Compliance     The Clery Act    Campus Security Authorities    Reporting Forms    Clery Governance     Clery Compliance Executive Committee (CCEC)    Clery Compliance Advisory Committee (CCAC)    UI Clery Coordination Council, Regional Committee        Continuity of Operations     University of Illinois Ready      Threat/Hazard Mitigation     Threat and Hazards Identification Risk Assessment    Hazard Mitigation Plan      Training & Exercising     Training Events    Multi-Year Training and Exercise Plan (MYTEP)    Exercises    Emergency Management Institute’s Curriculum     FEMA – Independent Study Courses    FEMA Student Identification Number (FEMA SID)    Incident Command    Continuity of Op